cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on exploring the bias towards texture in convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and its origins. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of different architectures, hyperparameters, and self-supervised training objectives on the bias, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses the decoding of hidden representations, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
